[This report was provided by Kathryn Soderholm <kathryn.soderholm@gmail.com>]

[Brazil has embarked in a race against time, vaccinating the population in affected areas before urban cycles with transmission by _Aedes aegypti_ mosquitoes can be initiated. So far, all cases have been attributed to spill-over from sylvan (forest) transmission. The quick response by health authorities so far has been successful in preventing urban transmission, but cases so near to a major population center such as Rio de Janeiro city, with abundant _Aedes aegypti_ populations, is worrisome.

Maps of Brazil can be accessed at http://s13.postimg.org/jumnalk87/map_of_Brazil.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4988191,6. - Mod.TY

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4988191,6.]
